terpretive\">\u003Cspan class=\"linenumber\">3\u003C/span>ζησεν\u003C/span>  \u003Cspan data-text=\"ἔτη\">ἔτη\u003C/span> · ἔνδεκα´ \u003Cbr id=\"al4-interpretive\">\u003Cspan class=\"linenumber\">4\u003C/span>\u003Cspan data-text=\"μῆνες\">μ\u003Cspan class=\"petraeligature\" title=\"Ligature: these characters are joined\">ῆ͡ν͡ε\u003C/span>ς\u003C/span> · θ´ \u003Cspan data-text=\"ἡμέρες\">ἡμέρες\u003C/span> · η´ · \u003Cbr id=\"al5-interpretive\">\u003Cspan class=\"linenumber\">5\u003C/span>\u003Cspan data-text=\"πατὴρ\">πα\u003Cspan class=\"petraeligature\" title=\"Ligature: these characters are joined\">τ͡ὴ\u003C/span>ρ\u003C/span>  \u003Cspan data-text=\"καὶ\">καὶ\u003C/span>  \u003Cspan data-text=\"μήτηρ\">μή\u003Cspan class=\"petraeligature\" title=\"Ligature: these characters are joined\">τ͡η\u003C/span>ρ\u003C/span>  \u003Cspan data-text=\"τέ ·κνῳ\">τέ - ·\u003Cbr id=\"al6-interpretive\">\u003Cspan class=\"linenumber\">6\u003C/span>κνῳ\u003C/span>  \u003Cspan data-text=\"γλυκυτάτῳ\">γλυκυτάτῳ\u003C/span>  \u003Cspan data-text=\"ἐποίησαν\">ἐποίησαν\u003C/span>  \u003C/span>\u003C/div>  \u003Cp class=\"miniapp\">\u003C/p>\u003C/div>\u003Cdiv id=\"edition-diplomatic\" lang=\"grc\">\u003Cdiv class=\"textpart\" lang=\"grc\">\u003Cspan class=\"ab\" id=\"div-diplomatic\">\u003Ca id=\"al1-diplomatic\">\u003C!--0-->\u003C/a>\u003Cspan class=\"linenumber\">1\u003C/span>·\u003Cspan data-text=\"Θεοῖς\">Θ\u003C/span>·\u003Cspan data-text=\"Καταχθονίοις\">Κ\u003C/span>·\u003Cbr id=\"al2-diplomatic\">\u003Cspan class=\"linenumber\">2\u003C/span>\u003Cspan data-type=\"persname\" data-name-type=\"attested\" data-text=\"Κασσία Βενοῦστα\">\u003Cspan data-type=\"name\" data-name-type=\"\" data-text=\"Κασσία\">ΚΑΣΣΙΑ\u003C/span>\u003Cspan data-type=\"name\" data-name-type=\"\" data-text=\"Βενοῦστα\">ΒΕΝΟΥΣΤΑ\u003C/span>\u003C/span>\u003Cspan data-text=\"ἔζησεν\">Ε\u003Cbr id=\"al3-diplomatic\">\u003Cspan class=\"linenumber\">3\u003C/span>ΖΗΣΕΝ\u003C/span>\u003Cspan data-text=\"ἔτη\">ΕΤΗ\u003C/span>·ΕΝΔΕΚΑ\u003Cbr id=\"al4-diplomatic\">\u003Cspan class=\"linenumber\">4\u003C/span>\u003Cspan data-text=\"μῆνες\">Μ\u003Cspan class=\"petraeligature\" title=\"Ligature: these characters are joined\">Η͡Ν͡Ε\u003C/span>Σ\u003C/span>·Θ\u003Cspan data-text=\"ἡμέρες\">ΗΜΕΡΕΣ\u003C/span>·Η·\u003Cbr id=\"al5-diplomatic\">\u003Cspan class=\"linenumber\">5\u003C/span>\u003Cspan data-text=\"πατὴρ\">ΠΑ\u003Cspan class=\"petraeligature\" title=\"Ligature: these characters are joined\">Τ͡Η\u003C/span>Ρ\u003C/span>\u003Cspan data-text=\"καὶ\">ΚΑΙ\u003C/span>\u003Cspan data-text=\"μήτηρ\">ΜΗ\u003Cspan class=\"petraeligature\" title=\"Ligature: these characters are joined\">Τ͡Η\u003C/span>Ρ\u003C/span>\u003Cspan data-text=\"τέ ·κνῳ\">ΤΕ- ·\u003Cbr id=\"al6-diplomatic\">\u003Cspan class=\"linenumber\">6\u003C/span>ΚΝΩ\u003C/span>\u003Cspan data-text=\"γλυκυτάτῳ\">ΓΛΥΚΥΤΑΤΩ\u003C/span>\u003Cspan data-text=\"ἐποίησαν\">ΕΠΟΙΗΣΑΝ\u003C/span>\u003C/span>\u003C/div>\u003Cp class=\"miniapp\">\u003C/p>\u003C/div>\u003C/div>  \u003Cdiv id=\"facsimile-images\">\u003Ch2>Facsimile Images\u003C/h2>\u003Ca href=\"ISic001306_tiled.tif\">\u003Cimg title=\"I.Sicily with the permission of the Assessorato Regionale dei Beni Culturali e dell’Identità Siciliana - Dipartimento dei Beni Culturali e dell’Identità Siciliana\" src=\"ISic001306_tiled-thumb.tif\">\u003C/a>\u003Ca href=\"ISic001306.jpg\">\u003Cimg title=\"I.Sicily with the permission of the Assessorato Regionale dei Beni Culturali e dell’Identità Siciliana - Dipartimento dei Beni Culturali e dell’Identità Siciliana\" src=\"ISic001306-thumb.jpg\">\u003C/a>\u003C/div>  \u003Cdiv id=\"apparatus\">\u003Ch4>Apparatus criticus\u003C/h4>\u003Cul>\u003Cli>\u003Cspan>\u003Cspan>Text based on photographs\u003C/span>\u003C/span>; \u003C/li>\u003Cli>\u003Cspan class=\"line 5\">line.5: \u003Cspan>Kaibel saw an ivy leaf at the end of the line, but it rather seems to be a triangle-shaped interpunct.\u003C/span>\u003C/span>\u003C/li>\u003C/ul>\u003C/div>  \u003Cdiv id=\"translation\">\u003Ch2>English translation\u003C/h2>\u003Cp class=\"translation-author\">\u003Ca href=\"https://orcid.org/0000-0001-5187-5163\">Marta Fogagnolo\u003C/a>\u003C/p>  \u003Cp>To the underworld spirits. Kassia Benousta, lived for 11 years, 9 months, and 8 days. Her father and mother made this for their sweetest child.\u003C/p>  \u003C/div>  \u003Cdiv id=\"translation\">\u003Ch2>Italian translation\u003C/h2>\u003Cp class=\"translation-author\">\u003Ca href=\"https://orcid.org/0000-0001-5187-5163\">Marta Fogagnolo\u003C/a>\u003C/p>  \u003Cp>Agli Dei inferi. Kassia Benousta visse 11 anni, 9 mesi e 8 giorni. Suo padre e sua madre realizzarono questo per la loro dolce figlia.\u003C/p>  \u003C/div>  \u003Cdiv id=\"commentary\">\u003Ch2>commentary\u003C/h2>  \u003Cp>The structure of the epitaph is the most frequent in pagan epitaphs, with the invocation to the underworld spirits, the name of the deceased in the nominative form, his/her age, the name of the dedicants (in this case, the parents) and the dedication verb in aorist (Korhonen 2004: 85-86). An interesting linguistic detail is the indication of months and days in the nominative and not in the accusative form (\u003Cspan class=\"lang\" lang=\"grc\">μῆνες, ἡμέρες\u003C/span>), which seems to be due to confusion with Latin where the nominative and accusative plural of \u003Cspan class=\"lang\" lang=\"la\">mensis\u003C/span> and \u003Cspan class=\"lang\" lang=\"la\">dies\u003C/span> correspond: for a similar confusion, see also SEG 44.0762 = \u003Ca href=\"http://sicily.classics.ox.ac.uk/inscription/ISic000641\" target=\"_blank\">ISic000641\u003C/a>. On the name \u003Cspan class=\"lang\" lang=\"grc\">Βενοῦστα\u003C/span>, see SEG 29.931-3 (from Morgantina, 1st century CE). Note too the spelling out of the first numeral in full, rather than using the standard alphabetic notation.\u003C/p>  \u003C/div>  \u003Cdiv id=\"bibliography\">\u003Ch2>bibliography\u003C/h2>  \u003Cul>\u003Cli>\u003C/li>\u003Cli> Spuches 1864 13 no.3 \u003Ca href=\"https://biblio.inscriptiones.org/epig10002042\" target=\"_blank\">https://biblio.inscriptiones.org/epig10002042\u003C/a>\u003C/li>\u003Cli> Kaibel 1890 \u003Ca href=\"https://clio.columbia.edu/catalog/6873760\" target=\"_blank\">483\u003C/a>  \u003Ca href=\"https://biblio.inscriptiones.org/epig10001072\" target=\"_blank\">https://biblio.inscriptiones.org/epig10001072\u003C/a>\u003C/li>\u003Cli> Korhonen 2004 67 \u003Ca href=\"https://biblio.inscriptiones.org/epig10000028\" target=\"_blank\">https://biblio.inscriptiones.org/epig10000028\u003C/a>\u003C/li>\u003C/ul>  \u003Cul>\u003Cli> Korhonen 2004 85-86 \u003Ca href=\"https://biblio.inscriptiones.org/epig10000028\" target=\"_blank\">https://biblio.inscriptiones.org/epig10000028\u003C/a>\u003C/li>\u003C/ul>  \u003C/div>  \u003Cdiv id=\"license\"> Licensed under a Creative Commons-Attribution 4.0 licence. \u003C/div>",[224,227,230,233,235,238,241],{"id":225,"html":226},"editions","\u003Cdiv id=\"edition-interpretive\" lang=\"grc\">  \u003Cdiv class=\"textpart\" lang=\"grc\">\u003Cspan class=\"ab\" id=\"div-interpretive\">  \u003Ca id=\"al1-interpretive\">\u003C!--0-->\u003C/a>\u003Cspan class=\"linenumber\">1\u003C/span>· \u003Cspan data-text=\"Θεοῖς\">Θ(εοῖς)\u003C/span> · \u003Cspan data-text=\"Καταχθονίοις\">Κ(αταχθονίοις)\u003C/span> · \u003Cbr id=\"al2-interpretive\">\u003Cspan class=\"linenumber\">2\u003C/span>\u003Cspan data-type=\"persname\" data-name-type=\"attested\" data-text=\"Κασσία Βενοῦστα\">\u003Cspan data-type=\"name\" data-name-type=\"\" data-text=\"Κασσία\">Κασσία\u003C/span>  \u003Cspan data-type=\"name\" data-name-type=\"\" data-text=\"Βενοῦστα\">Βενοῦστα\u003C/span>\u003C/span>  \u003Cspan data-text=\"ἔζησεν\">ἔ-\u003Cbr id=\"al3-interpretive\">\u003Cspan class=\"linenumber\">3\u003C/span>ζησεν\u003C/span>  \u003Cspan data-text=\"ἔτη\">ἔτη\u003C/span> · ἔνδεκα´ \u003Cbr id=\"al4-interpretive\">\u003Cspan class=\"linenumber\">4\u003C/spa