re joined\">Η͡Ν͡Ε\u003C/span>Σ\u003C/span>·Θ\u003Cspan data-text=\"ἡμέρες\">ΗΜΕΡΕΣ\u003C/span>·Η·\u003Cbr id=\"al5-diplomatic\">\u003Cspan class=\"linenumber\">5\u003C/span>\u003Cspan data-text=\"πατὴρ\">ΠΑ\u003Cspan class=\"petraeligature\" title=\"Ligature: these characters are joined\">Τ͡Η\u003C/span>Ρ\u003C/span>\u003Cspan data-text=\"καὶ\">ΚΑΙ\u003C/span>\u003Cspan data-text=\"μήτηρ\">ΜΗ\u003Cspan class=\"petraeligature\" title=\"Ligature: these characters are joined\">Τ͡Η\u003C/span>Ρ\u003C/span>\u003Cspan data-text=\"τέ ·κνῳ\">ΤΕ- ·\u003Cbr id=\"al6-diplomatic\">\u003Cspan class=\"linenumber\">6\u003C/span>ΚΝΩ\u003C/span>\u003Cspan data-text=\"γλυκυτάτῳ\">ΓΛΥΚΥΤΑΤΩ\u003C/span>\u003Cspan data-text=\"ἐποίησαν\">ΕΠΟΙΗΣΑΝ\u003C/span>\u003C/span>\u003C/div>\u003Cp class=\"miniapp\">\u003C/p>\u003C/div>",{"id":228,"html":229},"apparatus","\u003Ch4>Apparatus criticus\u003C/h4>\u003Cul>\u003Cli>\u003Cspan>\u003Cspan>Text based on photographs\u003C/span>\u003C/span>; \u003C/li>\u003Cli>\u003Cspan class=\"line 5\">line.5: \u003Cspan>Kaibel saw an ivy leaf at the end of the line, but it rather seems to be a triangle-shaped interpunct.\u003C/span>\u003C/span>\u003C/li>\u003C/ul>",{"id":231,"html":232},"translation","\u003Ch2>English translation\u003C/h2>\u003Cp class=\"translation-author\">\u003Ca href=\"https://orcid.org/0000-0001-5187-5163\">Marta Fogagnolo\u003C/a>\u003C/p>  \u003Cp>To the underworld spirits. Kassia Benousta, lived for 11 years, 9 months, and 8 days. Her father and mother made this for their sweetest child.\u003C/p>  ",{"id":231,"html":234},"\u003Ch2>Italian translation\u003C/h2>\u003Cp class=\"translation-author\">\u003Ca href=\"https://orcid.org/0000-0001-5187-5163\">Marta Fogagnolo\u003C/a>\u003C/p>  \u003Cp>Agli Dei inferi. Kassia Benousta visse 11 anni, 9 mesi e 8 giorni. Suo padre e sua madre realizzarono questo per la loro dolce figlia.\u003C/p>  ",{"id":236,"html":237},"commentary","\u003Ch2>commentary\u003C/h2>  \u003Cp>The structure of the epitaph is the most frequent in pagan epitaphs, with the invocation to the underworld spirits, the name of the deceased in the nominative form, his/her age, the name of the dedicants (in this case, the parents) and the dedication verb in aorist (Korhonen 2004: 85-86). An interesting linguistic detail is the indication of months and days in the nominative and not in the accusative form (\u003Cspan class=\"lang\" lang=\"grc\">μῆνες, ἡμέρες\u003C/span>), which seems to be due to confusion with Latin where the nominative and accusative plural of \u003Cspan class=\"lang\" lang=\"la\">mensis\u003C/span> and \u003Cspan class=\"lang\" lang=\"la\">dies\u003C/span> correspond: for a similar confusion, see also SEG 44.0762 = \u003Ca href=\"http://sicily.classics.ox.ac.uk/inscription/ISic000641\" target=\"_blank\">ISic000641\u003C/a>. On the name \u003Cspan class=\"lang\" lang=\"grc\">Βενοῦστα\u003C/span>, see SEG 29.931-3 (from Morgantina, 1st century CE). Note too the spelling out of the first numeral in full, rather than using the standard alphabetic notation.\u003C/p>  ",{"id":239,"html":240},"bibliography","\u003Ch2>bibliography\u003C/h2>  \u003Cul>\u003Cli>\u003C/li>\u003Cli> Spuches 1864 13 no.3 \u003Ca href=\"https://biblio.inscriptiones.org/epig10002042\" target=\"_blank\">https://biblio.inscriptiones.org/epig10002042\u003C/a>\u003C/li>\u003Cli> Kaibel 1890 \u003Ca href=\"https://clio.columbia.edu/catalog/6873760\" target=\"_blank\">483\u003C/a>  \u003Ca href=\"https://biblio.inscriptiones.org/epig10001072\" target=\"_blank\">https://biblio.inscriptiones.org/epig10001072\u003C/a>\u003C/li>\u003Cli> Korhonen 2004 67 \u003Ca href=\"https://biblio.inscriptiones.org/epig10000028\" target=\"_blank\">https://biblio.inscriptiones.org/epig10000028\u003C/a>\u003C/li>\u003C/ul>  \u003Cul>\u003Cli> Korhonen 2004 85-86 \u003Ca href=\"https://biblio.inscriptiones.org/epig10000028\" target=\"_blank\">https://biblio.inscriptiones.org/epig10000028\u003C/a>\u003C/li>\u003C/ul>  ",{"id":